and OFD decrees are partially referred to in the decree: FMS decree of content 1 10 3 1972 B / II-235/72 S-2000 / S-2130 / S-2188 A Doubts about the new regulation the land gain taxation by the 2 St\u00c4ndG 1971 2 3 5 1972 B / II-642/72 S-2230 A Definition of agricultural and forestry operations 3 9 6 1972 B / II-656/72 S-2130 / S-2188 A Determination of the higher partial value according to Section 55 (5) EStG 4 4 7 1972 B / II-656/72 S-2130 / S-2188 A Responsibility for the separate determination of land in accordance with Section 55 (5) EStG 5 7 7 1972 B / IV-390/72 S-3300 A Determination of the starting amounts according to Section 55 para 2 and 3 EStG by valuation bodies 6 Order of 29 8 1972 S-2130 / S-2188 - 8 - St 221 Determination of the starting amounts in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "of Section 55 Paragraphs 2 and 3 EStG 1971 for land belonging to agricultural and forestry assets 7 FMS decree of 11 11 1974 B / II-1025/74 S-2230 S-2188 A Time of recording the value of the land in the case of Stpfl with profit determination according to \u00a7 4 Paragraph 1 EStGI General information on land gain taxation1 Legal basis By the Second Tax Amendment Act 1971 of 10 8 1971 (BStBl IS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "373), the taxation of land gains for farmers and foresters, self-employed and small businesses has been newly regulated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "This new regulation essentially consists of the deletion of Section 4 (1) sentence 5 EStG, a supplement to Section 4 (3) EStG, an amendment to Section 14 EStG, the introduction of Section 14a EStG, an amendment to Section 16 (4) EStG, the Addition of a \u00a7 55 EStG, the insertion of transitional regulations in \u00a7 52 EStG, a supplement to \u00a7\u00a7 8 and 12 GDL (for financial years beginning after December 31, 1973, see \u00a7 13a Paragraph 6 EStG - BStBl 1974 IS"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "249)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 Temporal scope of application a) The new regulation only applies to farmers and foresters if the land has been sold or removed after 30 6 1970 (Section 52 (5) EStG 1971; Section 52 (3) EStG 1974; Section 52 (2) EStG 1975)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In the case of small businesses and self-employed persons, the land gain taxation applies if the land was sold or removed after August 14, 1971 (Section 52 (5) EStG 1971; Section 52 (3) EStG 1974; Section 52 (2) EStG 1975)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Note also to Section 16 (1) EStR 1972b) In the case of farmers and foresters as well as small businesses and self-employed people, increases in land value prior to 1 7 1970 are not taken into account when determining the profit on sale or withdrawal, even in cases where the Land already belonged to business assets on 30 6 1970 (Section 55 (1) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Example: If a small business owner sells his property belonging to the business assets before August 15, 1971, this transaction is not significant for income tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the land is sold after August 14, 1971, the new land gain taxation rules apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The increases in land value that occurred before 1 7 1970 are not to be taken into account, but the changes in value that occurred between 30 6 1970 and 15 8 1971 and up to the date of sale are to be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "3 Determination of advance payments In significant cases, the land gains resulting from the sale of the land are to be recorded not only as part of the assessment, but by adjusting the current advance payments or by subsequently increasing the advance payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "II Concept of agricultural and forestry operations 1 Serious agricultural and forestry activities The concept of agricultural and forestry operations does not require a minimum size or the affiliation of farm buildings and resources"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The serious agricultural use of individual agricultural properties is therefore also agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "According to No. 3 of the decree of 3 5 1972, for reasons of administrative simplification, it can generally be assumed that - apart from the so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Intensive use (vegetable, flower and ornamental plant cultivation, tree nurseries, viticulture, hops, asparagus and tobacco growing, fruit growing and forestry) there is no agricultural or forestry operation if the total land area under cultivation does not exceed 3000 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, the self-cultivated land area is more than 3000 square meters, then there is an agricultural and forestry operation if, according to the overall picture, these areas are used seriously for agricultural purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Indications for serious agricultural use can be the scope of the work, the use of machines and devices as well as the ongoing fertilization and spraying of the crops"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Membership in an agricultural professional organization, membership in agricultural purchasing and sales cooperatives, payment of contributions to the agricultural retirement fund, the use of cheaper gas oil and other state measures to improve the agricultural structure can all contribute to the existence of an agricultural and forestry business speak"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Agricultural use also exists if the products are only used for personal consumption"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In this case, however, serious use cannot be assumed on a regular basis because of the assumed low profitability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Are areas only managed in the interests of landscape protection (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "mowed by the owner or a third party), it can no longer be considered serious agricultural and forestry activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If these principles are applied, private house gardens, allotment gardens and weekend properties (see also decree of 3 5 1972) are excluded from the field of agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 Affiliation of land to the business assets The business assets of a farmer and forest manager include: a) the land owned by the business owner; economic ownership is sufficient (cf. Section III No. 2) b) Leased property c) The lowland (\u00a7 44 BewG), z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Heidelandd) Unland (\u00a7 45 BewG), z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Ditches and embankments) fallow land (social wasteland); These are properties that are temporarily not cultivated for personal or economic reasons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Regarding b) If individual properties of the remaining business are temporarily leased, they remain necessary business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, they are leased on a long-term basis, the removal of the property can be recognized with evidence of the lease (name of the lessee)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "A prerequisite for a tax-recognized withdrawal is that the lease has been seriously agreed and is actually carried out (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "for leases between parents and children)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the permanent lease took place before July 1, 1970 and the withdrawal was expressly declared, the land on July 1, 1970 belonged to private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the declaration has not been made, the same applies if a) at the time of the lease there was no reason for the lessor to declare the withdrawal for tax purposes (e.g. because"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "no assessment was carried out) or b) the rental income was shown in the tax return for the assessment period 1969 as income from rental and leasing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Because of the determination of the extraction value in the period up to 30 June 1972 see No. 11 of the decree of 10 3 1972 To e) If individual agricultural areas of an agricultural holding are not used for agricultural purposes for a definite or indefinite period, they generally remain business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If a farmer finally and recognizably ceases to use individual pieces of land, these pieces of land can be removed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "This can e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "be the case if the use was discontinued due to an assignment procedure or due to a development"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the cessation of use, a clear withdrawal action is a prerequisite"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "However, the treatment of the property in the standard value method is irrelevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If all areas of an agricultural holding are no longer used for agricultural purposes - also referred to in parlance as social fallow land - this can be a task for the holding"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Are allotments, which according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 34 (7) BewG, if this is an independent business that is permanently fallow, one can no longer speak of a serious agricultural and forestry activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "They therefore belong to private assets from the time of cessation of use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if a third party looks after the area (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "mows down)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The cessation of use will regularly be associated with an operational cessation (see Section V No. 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "3 Heritable building right The encumbrance of a property belonging to a business asset with a heritable building right does not in itself constitute a withdrawal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Land belonging to an agricultural and forestry business asset and which was encumbered with a heritable building right prior to 1 7 1970 therefore still belonged to the property owner's agricultural and forestry business assets on 1 7 1970"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Something different only applies if the owner sold his business before 17 1970 without the property encumbered with the heritable building right, gave up his business or removed the property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If there was neither a sale of a business, nor a cessation of business, nor a withdrawal before 1 7 1970, for reasons of the protection of legitimate expectations in accordance with the administrative instruction contained in No. 6 (1) of the decree of 10 3 1972, a withdrawal can be assumed before 1 7 1970 if the ground rent was treated as income from renting and leasing in the final assessment of the property owner for the assessment period 1969"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "4 Usufruct If a usufructuary right is established for an agricultural and forestry operation, the land belonging to the agricultural and forestry operation must be assigned to the legal owner (usufructuary buyer)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Something else only applies if the usufructuary is to be regarded as the beneficial owner of the property as an exception"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "That should z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "be the case if the owner orders the lifelong usufruct of an agricultural holding in favor of a person who is considerably younger than he and whom he has appointed as his sole heir (see also Section III No. 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The same applies when ordering a usufruct on individual agricultural and forestry properties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "5 examples of the 3000 sqm rule a) Several piece lands of a taxpayer The 3000 sqm limit does not refer to the individual piece land, but to all land areas of a taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "b) Lots of land belonging to a community of heirs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The decisive factor is therefore not the size of the parts of the property attributable to the individual participants, but the size of the entire agricultural holding"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "c) Application of the 3000 sqm regulation A taxpayer owns the following properties: aa) 2000 sqm arable land 1500 sqm weekend property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The weekend property is part of private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Since the arable land is no larger than 3000 square meters, it also counts as private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "bb) 500 sqm vineyard area 2000 sqm arable area The 3000 sqm regulation does not apply, as there is already an agricultural and forestry operation with regard to the vineyard area and therefore the arable area also represents business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "cc) 500 square meters of fallow vineyards 2000 square meters of yielding vineyards, owner-used 1600 square meters of forest 1500 square meters of tree meadow, owner-occupied 1200 square meters of tree meadow leased for DM 120 per year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the area used by the owner (including the fallow vineyards, the forest and the tree meadow) is larger than 3000 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "All of these areas belong to the agricultural business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "It can only be doubted how the leased meadow is to be treated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If it was already leased permanently on July 1, 1970, and the removal of the meadow was expressly declared before July 1, 1970, or if the lease income was declared in the 1969 income tax return as income from renting and leasing, then there are no concerns To accept private wealth"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, the meadow is only now leased on a long-term basis, it can be withdrawn with the result that profit is realized"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as vineyards are listed in the above examples, the decision is to be applied accordingly to other intensively used areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "III Land used for agriculture and forestry in civil-legal property of spouses and children1 General Land and forestry-used land belong to the business assets of an agriculture and forestry sector if they are in the civil-legal or economic property of the business owner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Land that belongs to the business owner's spouse is therefore not part of the business owner's business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 Economic ownership According to the BFH judgment of 26 1 1970 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "264) can only be accepted if the legal owner can be permanently excluded from affecting the economic property so that his claim to surrender no longer has any economic significance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "These prerequisites will only be met in exceptional cases for the property land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Such an exceptional case does not exist if one or both parents in his or her"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "their agricultural and forestry operations co-manage land belonging to a minor child; because the parents' administrative rights over the child's property do not permanently exclude the child from affecting the property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Even the free transfer of land from one spouse to the other spouse or the children to one or both parents does not constitute beneficial ownership"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "3 Property regime Allocation of areas of the spouse to the business assets of agriculture and forestry can result from agreements under property law or from an existing corporate relationship between the spouses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In the case of the property regime of the community of property (before July 1, 1958, the property regime of the general community of property), a distinction must be made between the common property and the conditional property"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the joint property of the spouses includes an agricultural and forestry business, according to the BFH rulings of 18 2 1959 (BStBl III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "263) and from 1 3 1966 (BStBl III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "277) to accept co-entrepreneurship between the spouses even without a special agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In this case, all property belonging to the spouses used for agricultural and forestry purposes is part of the business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether they belong to the common property or to the conditional property of a spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the land belongs to the common property, half of it is attributable to each spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Land belonging to a spouse's reserved property is fully attributable to this spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If an agricultural and forestry business belongs to the property of a spouse, the following applies to properties that are managed within the framework of this business: Properties that are part of the property of the owner are fully attributable to this property and are business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Properties belonging to the other spouse's reserved property are only to be assigned to this spouse and are not part of the business owner's business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Land belonging to the common property is to be allocated to half of each spouse and half to the business assets of the business owner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "4 Co-entrepreneurship A company relationship between spouses that has to be observed for tax purposes exists in the agricultural sector as well as in the commercial sector if both spouses actually contribute to the achievement of the company's purpose through cooperation, provision of capital or the transfer of economic goods, in particular land, as it would be the case in business with strange partners"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The contribution must not be of minor importance (cf. the BFH judgment of 3 August 1973 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "844)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "A company is founded by a) the express conclusion of a partnership agreement, b) the tacit behavior of the spouse, which expresses the will to conclude a partnership agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The objective characteristics of co-entrepreneurship - cooperation, transfer of assets - are not enough on their own"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, there is no co-entrepreneurship if the spouse working in the company - possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "surrenders property belonging to him to the other spouse for use on the basis of an employment contract"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "IV Transfer of an agricultural and forestry operation by way of anticipated succession1 Transfer of the operation with all essential operating principles If a taxpayer transfers the agricultural and forestry operation as a whole to a successor free of charge, Section 7 (1) EStDV shall apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The hidden reserves contained in the business assets cannot be realized"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the agricultural and forestry business transferred to the successor was leased in its entirety at the time of the transfer without an operational cessation having been declared, Section 7 (1) EStDV can also be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 Retention of company buildings or individual property areas a) If a taxpayer transfers the agricultural and forestry operations to a successor free of charge, but retains the company building, Section 7 (1) EStDV does not apply because the essential principles of the operation are not transferred to the successor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the land, the essential operating principles of an agricultural and forestry business also include the operating buildings and, as a rule, the living and dead inventory"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the company building is retained, a company as a whole is not transferred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Since only individual economic goods are handed over free of charge, while the company building is taken over into private assets, there is an operational cessation within the meaning of Section 16 (3) EStG (Section 139 (5) EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "b) If, in the case of a free transfer of business, not business buildings, but rather individual land areas that are to be treated as agricultural operations (because they cover more than 3,000 square meters) are retained for own management, Section 7 (1) EStDV can be applied if the retained land is in proportion are of subordinate importance to the transferred farm and the successor can continue the transferred farm as a living organism without new acquisitions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Example: The farm is operated on 9 hectares of land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Buildings and inventory are available"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer transfers the business to the son and retains 4000 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The matter is to be judged differently if no business within the meaning of Section 7 (1) EStDV, but only individual assets were transferred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Example: A taxpayer has two plots of land that are 4000 square meters or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "6000 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "He manages it himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "He donates the 6000 square meter property to his son, he continues to cultivate the 4000 square meter property himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The area retained is not of minor importance in relation to the area transferred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "No agricultural operation as a whole, but only a single asset is transferred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "There is a withdrawal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The retained property is an agricultural operation and therefore business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "c) If a farmer transfers his agricultural and forestry operations to a successor free of charge and retains land areas of less than 3,000 square meters for his own management, the simplification rule (see No. 3 of the decree of 3 5 1972) cannot be applied against the will of the taxpayer become"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Therefore the farmer must be given the right to choose"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "He can choose whether he wants to transfer the retained land into private assets or not"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the farmer declares that he has transferred the retained areas of less than 3000 square meters to private property, the hidden reserves contained in the transferred areas must be discovered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "This is where a free transfer of business within the meaning of Section 7 (1) EStDV and a tax-favored tax benefit under Section 14 34 EStG come together (Section 139 (5) EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, the farmer expressly declares that he has not transferred the retained land to private property, this continues to constitute an agricultural and forestry operation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In addition, there is a free transfer of business in accordance with Section 7 (1) EStDV"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the agricultural and forestry use of all areas belonging to the business (including those previously leased) is finally and objectively ceased, this is to be seen as a conclusive treatment of the business end without the need for a special declaration of abandonment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If operations were discontinued before 17/1970, the hidden reserves, insofar as they relate to the land, remain tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the company was discontinued after 1 7 1970 but before 1 7 1972, the rule contained in No. 11 of the decree of 10 3 1972 must generally be followed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If a farmer and forester leased all of the land to several tenants before 1 7 1970, then he regularly gave up his business before 1 7 1970"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "A special declaration of responsibility is not required in these cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "On July 1, 1970, the plots belong to private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "A continuation of the operation with the result that the lease income is to be treated as income from agriculture and forestry can only be accepted as an exception if the leasing of the individual areas is based on special circumstances and the lessor intends to resume operations and this possibility is sufficiently secured"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 Business leasing a) General The leasing of an agricultural and forestry business as a whole can be permitted according to the decree of 17 12 1965 - III-B / II-Tgb"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "No. 512/65 - S-2140 A communicated by order of 28 12 1965 S-2140 - 16 - St 221 (lease decree) can only be accepted if the essential operating principles (operation with buildings, land and dead and living inventory) are as be leased as a single whole"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer has the option of ceasing to operate either at the beginning of the lease or at any later point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the company was operated by several people, the declaration of duties must be submitted uniformly by all those involved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "According to the decree of 10 3 1972 No. 6, in the cases of company leasing mentioned there, in which the lease income was treated as income from renting and leasing in the legally binding assessment for 1969, it can be assumed that the company was closed before 17 1970"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of the protection of legitimate expectations, this also applies if the lease income was declared in the 1969 income tax return as income from renting and leasing, but the tax office did not carry out an assessment and a declaration of discontinuation of operation possible according to No. 4 of the decree of 3 5 1972 was not submitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "b) Withdrawal of individual pieces of land If an agricultural and forestry business is leased while the business is being continued, the land belonging to the landlord and leased are necessary business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Their removal is therefore only possible if they leave the leased business, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "are no longer co-leased due to a change in the lease agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the land that belongs to the lessor and which is also leased is sold, then they are removed from the business assets of the lessor through the sale"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "c) Retention of individual pieces of land If a farmer and forester who leases his business as a whole retains land areas for further management that are of minor importance in relation to the total area (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "6000 square meters are retained from a total area of \u200b\u200b10 hectares), then this is entirely harmless for the acceptance of a business lease"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Since - as already stated in II - every small area can, strictly speaking, represent an agricultural and forestry operation, two agricultural and forestry operations were created by leasing the operation to the exclusion of individual areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "On the one hand, there is a lease of the business as a whole (with the option of explaining the task or continuing the operation), on the other hand, the retained area forms a separate agricultural and forestry operation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "From this, in turn, individual areas can be leased permanently and therefore - as explained in II 2 - removed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the retained area is no more than 3000 square meters, no more agricultural and forestry operations exist according to No. 3 of the decree of 3 5 1972"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Since the area was previously a business asset, the farmer cannot be forced to transfer it to private assets when the lease begins"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The farmer is to be given the right to choose whether he wants to keep the area in the business assets or remove it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the area remains business assets, the case must be specially monitored in the future, since in the event of a sale in view of the 3000 square meter regulation, it could be overlooked that it is agricultural business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the farmer transfers the retained area when leasing the business or at a later point in time into private assets, the resulting profit is favored according to Sections 14 and 34 of the Income Tax Act, as the self-cultivated area is now being closed down"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Were the retained assets an essential operating basis, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "the farm building or a large cultivation area, the lease waiver cannot be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "It concerns the leasing of individual assets of the continuing operation, which the taxpayer can permanently withdraw in the case of a lease or remain in his business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The leased land can also remain in the business assets of taxpayers who determine their profit in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStG or the GDL"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In the case of these taxpayers, according to Section 14 (6) of the Income Tax Act 1972, voluntary business assets are not considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Since the land was originally part of the business assets, according to Section 14, Paragraph 13 of the 1972 Income Tax Act, it can only be removed from the business assets through a clear removal process"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Examples: a) A farmer (part-time) has an area of \u200b\u200b8,000 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "He leases 4,000 square meters of this on a permanent basis, and manages the remaining 4,000 square meters himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "He can choose whether he wants to leave the leased 4000 sqm in his business assets or remove it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If he withdraws the leased 4000 sqm, the withdrawal profit is current profit (no discount according to \u00a7\u00a7 14 34 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The remaining 4000 square meters, which he manages himself, are still a business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "b) A farmer has an area of \u200b\u200b6000 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "He leases 4000 square meters on a permanent basis and continues to manage 2000 square meters himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer can leave the leased 4000 square meters in his business assets or withdraw it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If he removes the leased 4000 square meters, he in turn has the right to choose whether he wants to transfer the remaining 2000 square meters into his private assets or leave them as business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If he leaves the remaining 2000 square meters in business assets, a withdrawal profit belongs to the possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "4000 sqm withdrawn to current profit and is not favored according to \u00a7\u00a7 14 34 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "However, if he transfers the entire area into his private assets, the total profit is favored according to \u00a7\u00a7 14 34 EStG (business closure)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "d) Lease of piece lands If a taxpayer only owns a piece of land which, apart from the 3000 sqm rule, represents an agricultural and forestry operation, and if he has leased this piece land on a permanent basis, one would have to come to the conclusion when applying the lease decree that the piece land is a continued operation of agriculture and forestry if the taxpayer has not submitted a declaration of abandonment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In this regard, the view must be taken that the lease decree is not to be applied without restriction to piece land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "An agricultural and forestry business in the whole of i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "of the lease decree can only be a business with buildings and inventory, since only such a business can be continued as a living organism by a tenant without new acquisitions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If such a piece of land was leased before July 1, 1970, it belonged to the taxpayer's private assets on that date and is not subject to land gain taxation when it is sold"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If a piece of land was leased after 30 6 1970, then this lease can regularly be seen as a cessation of operation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "However, the taxpayer cannot be prevented from continuing the piece landings as business assets even after the lease"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If he declares that he wants to continue the business, the tax case must be specially monitored in the future, since in the event of a later sale, a taxable profit may arise, which is beneficiary according to \u00a7\u00a7 14 34 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If a taxpayer leases all of his previously agriculturally used land to several tenants and he no longer operates agriculture or forestry himself, an operational cessation is i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 14 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Section 16 (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "A special declaration of responsibility is not required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "VI Determination of the book values \u200b\u200bof the land according to \u00a7 55 Paragraph 1 to 4 EStG1 General Reference is made to the wording of \u00a7 55 Paragraph 1 to 4 EStG and to No. 10 of the decree of 10 3 1972"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 starting amounts according to \u00a7 55 para 2 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "1 and 2 to 8 EStG in cases in which the actual use on July 1, 1970 deviates from the use entered in the real estate cadastre"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the taxpayer proves that the actual use of areas on July 1, 1970 deviates from the use entered in the real estate cadastre, and if there are no yield indicators for these areas in the real estate cadastre, the starting amount must be determined in accordance with Section 55 (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The aforementioned legal provision regulates the cases mentioned conclusively"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "A later correction of the thus determined starting amounts after carrying out the land appraisal and determining the yield figures is not possible (see No. 10 Paragraph 9 of the decree of 10 3 1972)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "VII Determination of the higher partial value according to \u00a7 55 Paragraph 5 EStG1 Application, determination and determination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 86 AO possible) at the company tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Evidence can be provided in different ways: reference to comparable property sales, to a development plan existing on 1 July 1970, appraisal of the municipality"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "For further details, reference is made to No. 11 of the decree of 10 3 1972 and the decree of 9 6 1972"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 Simplification regulation In No. 11 of the decree of 10 3 1972 it was determined that in the case of sales or withdrawals before 1 7 1972 it can be assumed that the partial value of the land on 1 7 1970 is usually the sale price or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The withdrawal value corresponds, unless special circumstances (cf. decree of 9 6 1972) have led to a significant increase in value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Such value-increasing circumstances always exist when the sales price or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "the withdrawal value by more than 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "deviates upwards from the partial value on 1 7 1970"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to business sales or business closures before 1 7 1972. If the simplification rule comes into play, a formal determination of the higher partial value (in the amount of the sales proceeds minus the sales costs or sales costs) can be made in sales or withdrawal cases up to 30 6 1972"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "the withdrawal value)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "But this has to be put on record"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "3 Effects of the determination on other types of tax The determination of a higher partial value for the land can, according to Section 69 (4) BewG (from 1 1 1974), mean that the property must be added to the real estate in the course of a subsequent determination (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "if arable land became building land)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "This subsequent assessment has effects in individual cases on the property tax, u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Property tax and inheritance tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "However, the attribution to agricultural and forestry assets does not change if the increase in value is based on reasons that are to be sought in the agricultural sector"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "VIII Loss clause The loss clause of Section 55, Paragraph 6 of the Income Tax Act is intended to prevent book losses, which arise due to the application of the flat-rate value above the partial value, from reducing profits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Thereafter, losses may not be taken into account if the selling price after deducting the selling costs is less than twice the starting amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The prohibition of deductions also applies to partial value depreciation (see No. 13 of the decree of 10 3 1972)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Example: Double the starting amount 5000 DM Sale price 3000 DM The loss of 2000 DM is not deductible according to Section 55 (6) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "IX Book and value recording of the land1 What is the value recording of the land for taxpayers with profit determination according to \u00a7\u00a7 4 Abs 1 4 Abs 3 EStG or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "when determining profits in accordance with the GDL (\u00a7 13a EStG) is to be observed in general, results from the decree of 10 3 1972 on the statements in nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "1 2 and 12 of the decree are pointed out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In deviation from No. 1 (3) of the decree of 10 3 1972, the property belonging to the business assets is in the balance sheets, which are drawn up on a key date after 30 12 1975 (previously 30 12 1973), with the values \u200b\u200baccording to \u00a7 55 EStG to be shown"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 Paragraph 55 of the EStG only applies in cases in which the land was part of the fixed assets by the end of June 30, 1970"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If land is only acquired after June 30, 1970, the land must be capitalized at the cost of acquisition"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If land is laid, the deposit is to be assessed at the partial value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Deposits are to be carried at the most at the acquisition or production costs if the inserted asset was purchased within the last three years prior to the contribution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the land was acquired as private assets before 6/30/1970 and deposited after 6/30/1970 and within the three-year period, the deposit is double the starting amount according to \u00a7 55 Paragraph 1 to 4 EStG or the higher partial value according to \u00a7 55 Paragraph 5 EStG to be assessed if these values \u200b\u200bare higher than the acquisition costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The use of these values \u200b\u200bis justified because increases in land value that occurred prior to 1 7 1970 cannot be recorded by the land gain taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "X Taxation of land gains1 In the case of profit determination according to \u00a7 4 Paragraph 3 EStG and \u00a7 12 GDL (\u00a7 13a EStG) with payment in installments According to \u00a7 4 Paragraph 3 Sentence 4 EStG in the version of the Second Tax Amendment Act 1971, the acquisition or manufacturing costs for non-depreciable assets are fixed assets to be taken into account as a business expense only at the time of the sale or removal of these assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "If the entire selling price does not flow in the year of the sale, but - as is the case in particular with installment payments - at a later point in time, the taxpayer has the right to choose whether to consider the acquisition costs at the time of the sale of the property as operating expenses (Section 4 Para 3 sentence 4 EStG) and record the sales proceeds at the inflow (Section 11 (1) sentence 1 EStG) or whether he wants to tax the sales gain only at the point in time at which the sales proceeds exceed the acquisition costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The right to choose applies both to the determination of profits in accordance with Section 4 (3) EStG and to the determination of a profit surcharge in accordance with Section 12 (4) no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "3 GDL and is also relevant in those cases in which the property was part of the fixed assets on 1 7 1970 and was valued at twice the starting amount or the higher partial value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Summarizing example: A farmer who bought the property in 1973 for 70,000 DM and sells it in 1978 for 150,000 DM agrees with the buyer that the purchase price is to be paid in five annual installments of 30,000 DM each beginning in 1979"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The farmer has the following options: operating income 1978 0 operating expenses 1978 DM 70,000 = 70,000 DM loss operating income 1979 DM 30,000 operating expenses 1979 0 = 30,000 DM profit 1980 to 1983 as 1979 or: operating income 1979 DM 30,000 operating expenses 1979 DM 30,000 = 01 980 as 1979 operating income 1981 DM 30,000 operating expenses 1981 DM 10,000 = DM 20,000 Profit operating income 1982 DM 30,000 operating expenses 1982 0 = DM 30,000 profit 1983 as in 19822 In the case of structural change between the views of the I and IV Senate of the BFH on the question of how the book approach \"Land is to be treated when a commercial enterprise through a structural change to an agricultural and forestry one Operation becomes (or vice versa) \"there was a fundamental difference (see FMS decree of 30 5 1974 B / II - 973/74 - S-2135 A, announced by order of 20 6 1974 S-2135 - 30 - St 221 -)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "By resolution of October 7, 1974, BStBl 1975 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "168 the legal questions submitted to him were decided as follows: 1 The structural change of a horticultural company from a commercial enterprise with profit determination according to \u00a7 5 EStG to an agricultural enterprise with profit determination according to \u00a7 4 para 1 EStG a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "is not a removal of the land used for the business from the commercial business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 In the event of a structural change of the type described, the hidden reserves contained in the book approach for the land are not to be dissolved either from the point of view of an operational discontinuation or for any other reason"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "XI Exemptions according to \u00a7\u00a7 14 14a EStG1 General The exemption according to \u00a7 14 EStG has been increased from the assessment period 1971 in accordance with the amendment of \u00a7 16 para 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In addition, \u00a7 14a EStG was inserted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "According to this, special allowances are granted for certain sales transactions between July 1, 1970 and December 31, 1973"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "For details, please refer to nos"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "7 and 8 of the decree of 10 3 1972 and the Second Tax Amendment Act 1973 of 18 7 1974 (BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "521)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 Special features a) Relevant unit value when applying Section 14a Paragraphs 1 to 3 EStG in lease cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "presupposes that the unit value of the business applicable at the time of the sale is 25,000 DM or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Does not exceed 30,000 DM (see Section 14a Paragraph 1 in conjunction with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "of the Second Tax Amendment Act 1973 of 18 7 1974 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "It is of the opinion that in the case of leased holdings, the determination of the unit value limit is not based on the total unit value, but rather on the lessor's share for the lessor and on the lessee's share of the unit value for the lessee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The unit value limit can only meaningfully relate to what the farmer and forestry owner who wants to claim the tax allowance can sell in a legally permissible manner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "b) Application of Section 14a, Paragraph 3 of the Income Tax Act (EStG) in cases of lease The business is also considered to be sold if a tenant or other beneficial owner hands over the agricultural and forestry business to the owner for the purpose of structural improvement (cf. decree of 15 3 1973 - B / II- 402/73 - S-2239 A, announced by order of 28 3 1973 S-2239 3 St 221)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "c) Repayment of debts of another agricultural and forestry enterprise According to \u00a7 14a Abs 4 EStG an allowance is granted if only part of the land belonging to an agricultural and forestry enterprise is sold"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for the granting of the exemption is"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "that the sale price will be used to pay off debts of the agricultural and forestry business within six months of the sale"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The tax exemption is only to be granted if the debts of the agricultural and forestry company, whose business assets included the property sold, are repaid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The repayment of debts of another company of the same taxpayer is not tax-favored according to the wording of \u00a7 14a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "d) Compensation for deviating heirs within the meaning of Section 14a Paragraph 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "are granted if the sale price is used to compensate for heirs within six months of the sale"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "This requirement is fulfilled if co-heirs are compensated due to an inheritance dispute, a person entitled to a compulsory portion is paid out or a legatee who would be entitled to inheritance according to the legal succession receives a legacy"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Other legatees, on the other hand, cannot be regarded as heirs giving way within the meaning of this provision"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "e) Effect of the application for the granting of an exemption within the meaning of Section 14a (4) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 14a Paragraph 4 EStG, which is part of current profit in the case of a business year deviating from the calendar year according to \u00a7 2 Paragraph 6 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "1 sentence 1 EStG (\u00a7 4a Paragraph 2 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "1 sentence 1 EStG 1975) on a pro rata basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to the exemption amount i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 14a Paragraph 4 EStG (No. 8 Paragraph 6 of the Decree of 10 3 1972)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The exemption is only granted on application"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The request relates to the entire capital gain"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, even if the tax exemption is distributed over two calendar years, only one application is required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "A limitation of the application to the pro-rata capital gain of a calendar year is not considered admissible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "f) Offsetting of the tax allowance according to \u00a7 14a Abs 4 EStG when applying the concessions according to \u00a7\u00a7 6b, 6c EStG If the tax relief according to \u00a7 14a Abs 4 EStG is used for a capital gain, \u00a7 6b or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "6c EStG for the part of the capital gain that is not tax-exempt under Section 14 (4) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "g) Severance payments before the handover of the business. Severance payments that are paid to any future heirs before the handover to the intended heir are not considered severance payments i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 14a Paragraph 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "h) Further requirements for the granting of the tax exemption according to \u00a7 14a Abs 4 EStG for sales of land after December 31, 1973 and before December 1, 1977 (Second Tax Amendment Act 1973)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The granting of the tax exemption according to \u00a7 14a Paragraph 4 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "of the Second Tax Amendment Act 1973 for sales after December 31, 1973 depends u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "also on the amount of income (24,000 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "48,000 DM) without taking into account the tax exemption (see letter e) in the assessment period prior to the sale"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Example: Preliminary remark: It is assumed that the taxpayer is assessed together with his spouse according to \u00a7 26 26b EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The profit determined in accordance with Section 4 (1) of the EStG for the 1973/74 financial year is DM 52,000. This profit includes a profit of DM 42,000 from the sale of land belonging to the business assets in March 1974"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer applies for an exemption in accordance with Section 14a (4) EStG in the amount of the capital gain"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisites of \u00a7 14a para 4 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "1 EStG are available"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The income from 1973, which is decisive for granting the tax exemption, is made up as follows: Income from agriculture and forestry a) pro rata profit for the 1972/73 financial year DM 7,000 b) pro rata profit in the 1973/74 financial year DM 26,000 c) other income DM 13,000 DM 46,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Exemption according to Section 13 (3) EStG DM 2,400 Total income DM 43,600"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Special expenses 3,600 DM Income 40,000 DM without deduction of the pro rata tax exemption according to \u00a7 14a Paragraph 4 EStG of 21,000 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Since the relevant income does not exceed the limit of 48,000 DM, the exemption according to \u00a7 14a Ab"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "4 EStG of a total of DM 42,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The tax exemption is to be taken into account in the assessments for 1973 and 1974 with DM 21,000 each when determining income from agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "i) Granting of the exemption according to \u00a7 14a Abs 4 EStG in the case of the uniform and separate determination of the income from agriculture and forestry If the income from agriculture and forestry is determined uniformly and separately, the time of the respective sale is also included in the notification of assessment for the first time for 1973 as well as the profits according to \u00a7 14a Abs 4 EStG especially for the calendar year in which the financial year begins and for the calendar year in which the financial year ends"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "XII Implementation of the taxation of land gains The processing of sales and withdrawals, which are to be checked for tax liability according to \u00a7 55 EStG, is often very laborious and time-consuming, especially since the taxpayers often do not cooperate sufficiently"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In the interest of simplifying work and speeding up processing, I therefore agree that in cases in which agricultural land has been sold, the following procedure will be followed: 1 If the sale price is not more than double the starting amount (Section 55 (1) EStG), there is nothing to be done"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The notification of sale must be filed with a corresponding note, which is signed by the department head"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Provided that for each municipality (in the case of larger municipalities for each district) the lowest double the starting amount (the yield figure multiplied by eight) for agricultural areas is determined and the sub-districts responsible for processing the land gain taxation for farmers and foresters are disclosed, in individual cases the determination of double the starting amount can also be refrained from, provided that the selling price does not exceed the lowest double starting amount determined for the respective municipality (district)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "I would therefore ask you to check whether it is appropriate to determine the lowest double the starting amount from this point of view"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 If the sale price exceeds twice the starting amount, a distinction must be made as to whether the sale took place before 1 7 1972 or after"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "a) Sale before July 1, 1972 aa) If the findings of the tax office show that the selling price of the property corresponds to the partial value on July 1, 1970, there will be no profit when carrying out the assessment procedure according to Section 55 (5) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) If there is no tax interest, this determination must be put on record on the notification of sale and finally signed by the department head"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the taxpayer can in principle dispense with the implementation of a determination procedure in accordance with Section 55 (5) EStG and the submission of the necessary application"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Likewise, in these cases, the often time-consuming investigations into whether the sold agriculturally used property is business or private property can be omitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "However, if the taxpayer has submitted an application to determine the higher partial value, the determination procedure must be carried out in accordance with Section 55 (5) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "bb) If, due to special circumstances, it can be assumed that the selling price exceeds the higher partial value of the land on 1 7 1970, I would ask the taxpayer to first inform the taxpayer of the right to apply under Section 55 (5) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "After receipt of the Stpfl's application, the determination procedure according to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "To initiate and implement Section 55 (5) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "b) Sale after June 30, 1972 If agricultural land was sold after August 30, 1972, the higher partial value as of July 1, 1970 can only be used if the Stpfl has submitted a corresponding application and the higher partial value has been determined separately is"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In this case, too, it is advisable to inform the Stpfl of the possibility of applying under Section 55 (5) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "3 In the case of the closure of the business or the removal of agriculturally used land, however, with a view to the fact that the Stpfl remains the owner of the land and that there is a greater interest in clear treatment, the separate assessment procedure pursuant to Section 55 (5) EStG can in principle be avoided not be waived for reasons of simplicity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "This applies regardless of whether the business closure is still effective on 30 6 1972 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "the removal took place before July 1, 1972 and whether there are any special circumstances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "XIII Determination of taxable cases1 The inquiries and notifications from Stpfl about operational tasks or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Conversion of real estate into private assets as well as unfinished sales notifications are to be evaluated using the forms attached as Annex 1 and 2 (Questionnaire I and Questionnaire II)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Questionnaire I is intended for the evaluation of the notices of sale"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Questionnaire II is to be used in those cases in which Stpfl or their advisors have submitted so-called statements of responsibility or other notifications about the fact that land belongs to private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The correspondence arising in this connection must be filed in the standard value files of the relevant tax authority in all cases that are not kept for income tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "In the income tax cases, the original documents for the income tax files and (due to possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Deletion of the StNr or cleaning of the income tax files) photocopies to the valuation files"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The forms are to be sent to the Stpfl in duplicate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The incoming questionnaires are to be evaluated promptly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "It is particularly important to check whether advance income tax payments are to be set"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 A sample of the newly issued form \"Notification of sale from the real estate transfer tax office\" is attached as Appendix 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The form has been adapted to the requirements of land gain taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The notification of sale intended for the tax office (assessment office) of the seller must first be forwarded by the GrESt office to the valuation office in future"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The assessment body must supplement the notification with the information necessary for the taxation of land gains before forwarding it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The sale notification intended for the purchaser's tax files must (as before) be sent by the GrESt office directly to the purchaser's local tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "The forms for 1 u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "2 are produced centrally and an estimated edition will be sent to the tax offices after completion"}, {"meta": {"name": "0019421.xml"}, "text": "Income tax / wage tax / church tax Saarland body gw-31"}]